color-foreground.description: Default text color for main content. Suitable for primary headings and body text.

color-foreground-secondary.description: Secondary text such as subheadings or supplementary content.

color-foreground-success.description: Applied to positive messages or indicators.

color-foreground-warning.description: Applied messages or indicators that require attention.

color-foreground-error.description: Applied to negative messages or indicators.

color-foreground-info.description: Applied to informative messages or indicators.

color-foreground-muted.description: Less prominent text like metadata or notes.

color-foreground-inverse.description: Text on dark backgrounds. Ideal for dark backgrounds.

color-background-layout.description: Main layout areas like body or page backgrounds.

color-background.description: Default surface background for most areas.

color-background-lowered.description: Use when you need a layer to appear lower than the main surface, e.g., progress bar.

color-border-warning.description: Border for warnings or cautionary elements.

color-border-error.description: Border for errors or critical alerts.

color-border-success.description: Border for success indicators or messages.
